                        <p class=""card-text"">Mass = 1,600 kilograms </p>
                        <p class=""card-text"">Speed = 25 miles per hour <strong>or</strong> 11 metres per second<sup>2</sup></p>
                        <p class=""card-text"">
                            It's worth working out the squared before putting it into the equation, so
                            11 x 11 = 121
                        </p>
                        <p><b>E<sub>k </sub>= 0.5 x 1,600 x 121</b></p>
                        <p><u>putting this in a calculator;</u> <b>E<sub>k </sub>= 96,800 joules of energy</b></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class=""row justify-content-center"">
                <div class=""card bg-light mb-3"" style=""max-width: 60rem;"">
                    <div class=""card-header"">50 miles per hour</div>
                    <div class=""card-body"">
                        <h1 class=""card-title"">E<sub>k</sub> = ");
            WriteLiteral(@"½mv<sup>2</sup></h1>
                        <p class=""card-text"">We will keep m the same but v is now increased from 30mph to 70mph.</p>
                        <p class=""card-text"">Mass = 1,600 kilograms </p>
                        <p class=""card-text"">Speed = 50 miles per hour <strong>or</strong> 22 metres per second<sup>2</sup></p>
                        <p class=""card-text"">
                            It's worth working out the squared before putting it into the equation, so
                            22 x 22 = 484
                        </p>
                        <p><b>E<sub>k </sub>= 0.5 x 1,600 x 484</b></p>
                        <p><u>putting this in a calculator;</u> <b>E<sub>k </sub>= 387,200 joules of energy</b></p>
                    </div>
