            WriteLiteral(@"gle=""tooltip"" data-placement=""top""
                   title=""A constant is as it sounds - constant. This means a number that we can use and it shouldn't change."">
                    constant
                </a>. The Earth's gravitational field strength is 9.81 N/kg, which means for every kilogram of an object's mass, it
                has a force of 9.81 Newtons pulling it to the ground. This is approximately the force required to hold up a
                10kg dumb bell a metre in the air.
            </p>
